### `patch()` - Partial Object Updates

A utility for partial object updates in `signal.set()`. Cleaner alternative to the spread pattern.

```tsx
const person = signal({ name: "John", age: 30, city: "NYC" });

// Partial object update
person.set(patch({ name: "Jane" }));
person.set(patch({ name: "Jane", age: 25 }));

// Key-value update  
person.set(patch("name", "Jane"));
person.set(patch("age", 25));

// Equivalent to (but shorter):
person.set(prev => ({ ...prev, name: "Jane" }));
```

**Features:**
- Type-safe with `Partial<T>` for partial objects
- Type-safe key-value with inferred value type
- Immutable - creates new object reference
- Preserves unmodified nested references

**When to use `patch()` vs alternatives:**

| Method | Use Case |
|--------|----------|
| `patch()` | Simple property updates, one-off changes |
| `focus.lens()` | Repeated access to same property |
| `immer` | Complex nested mutations |

